long_desc.thetext:
Steps to reproduce:

  var atom = new qx.ui.basic.Atom();
  atom.setSpace( 20, 100, 20, 25 );
  atom.setBorder( "black" );
  atom.setLabel( "foo" );
  atom.addToDocument();
  ...
  oldParent = atom.getParent();
  atom.setParent( null ); // Atom disappears
  ...
  atom.setLabel( "" ); // getLabel() returns "" now
  ...
  atom.setParent( oldParent ); // Atom re-appears displaying "foo"

A similar problem exists also with icons. We have this problem quite often when we reuse widgets from a pool. Although this might be an uncommon use case, I consider these a valid series of API calls.

These lines from Widget.js (method _handleDisplayable) may be the reason for this bug but I am not sure if we break things if we change it ;-(

      if (this._isDisplayable == vDisplayable && !(vDisplayable && vHint == "parent")) {
        return true;
      }
